DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T153000
SUMMARY:Hiking\, Pancakes\, and Maple Syrup!
DESCRIPTION:These Boots Are Made for Hiking\n**Meet Up Point: Car Park at 
 Orchard Community Park in Burlington**\n**Across the road from 5908 Blue S
 pruce Ave\, Burlington\, ON. L7L 6T3**\n\nJoin us for hiking and the Maple
  Syrup festival in Bronte Creek. Here's how it works!\nWe meet at 10:30 an
 d start hiking Bronte Creek trail with boots on the ground. What a wonderf
 ul trail that follows some great creeks\, ridges\, and plenty of nature. T
 he trail goes on and on from climbing and ravine lookouts\, and the group 
 will enjoy the variety of experiences here. Folks should plan to spend bet
 ween three and five hours hiking. It is common to see an array of animals 
 here\, including turkey\, eagles\, foxes\, coyotes\, and even some of the 
 cows in pastures.\nBetween 1:00 and 1:30 we will stop for lunch. For those
  who would like to experience the Maple Syrup Festival they head out with 
 James for a pancake lunch.\nFor keen hikers who would like to keep going\,
  you will continue with Mo for a full days hike.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/these-boots-are-made-for-hiking/event
 s/313883399/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260321T154809Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260321T154809Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
